<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-08-24T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-08-24T16:00:00-05:00" n="147" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">822.00/791: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-24T16:00:00-05:00">August 24, 1931—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 25—1:03 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>37. Congress has just accepted resignation of President of Ecuador.
                            Following prior resignation of Cabinet, Colonel Luis Larrea Alba was
                            appointed Minister of Gobernacion and automatically under the
                            constitution becomes Acting President. However, this appointment has not
                            been well received by the people. Situation still continues
                            uncertain.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>